OL,6,GAround 250 people attended a public
OL,7,Gmeeting in Derry-Londonderry this
OL,8,Gevening, organised by the NUJ, to voice
OL,9,Gtheir opposition to BBC Northern
OL,10,GIreland plans to scale back the news
OL,11,Goperation at local radio station BBC
OL,12,GRadio Foyle.
OL,14,FIn November, BBC Northern Ireland
OL,15,Fannounced that it was cutting 36 jobs
OL,16,Fin the region ` mainly in news and
OL,17,Fradio ` with eight journalist posts
OL,18,Fbeing removed at the Derry station.
OL,3,CLocals voice opposition to BBC Radio
OL,4,CFoyle cuts at public meeting
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G1/6
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34202
SC,0002
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F342A1673045701
OL,6,FRadio Foyle's breakfast programme faces
OL,7,Fthe axe, along with its hourly news
OL,8,Fbulletins.
OL,10,FLocal politicians, business people and
OL,11,Fclergy have voiced their opposition to
OL,12,Fthe plans.
OL,14,FFoyle MP Colum Eastwood said it was "an
OL,15,Fattempt to close BBC Radio Foyle down
OL,16,Fby stealth."
OL,18,FThe DUP's Gregory Campbell said the
OL,19,Fchange would lead to the BBC operation
OL,20,Fin Northern Ireland becoming
OL,21,F"Belfast-centric".
OL,3,CLocals voice opposition to BBC Radio
OL,4,CFoyle cuts at public meeting
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G2/6
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34203
SC,0003
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F342A1673045701
OL,6,FBBC Northern Ireland said that its
OL,7,Fplans "reflect a BBC-wide strategy to
OL,8,Fprioritise digital content, announced
OL,9,Fearlier this year, and the need to
OL,10,Fmanage inflationary and other cost
OL,11,Fpressures".
OL,13,FAt this evening's public meeting,
OL,14,FSeamus Dooley, NUJ assistant general
OL,15,Fsecretary, thanked the city's mayor,
OL,16,FSandra Duffy, for her strong
OL,17,Fendorsement of the union's campaign to
OL,18,Fsave the local radio station.
OL,3,CLocals voice opposition to BBC Radio
OL,4,CFoyle cuts at public meeting
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G3/6
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34204
SC,0004
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F342A1673045701
OL,6,FHe went on: "BBC Radio Foyle matters
OL,7,Fbecause community matters and tonight
OL,8,Fyou join with us as a community
OL,9,Frejecting an ill-conceived, half-baked
OL,10,Fplan which threatens to undermine the
OL,11,Fessence of the station, it's locally
OL,12,Fbased news service and the morning
OL,13,Fplatform which shapes the day of so
OL,14,Fmany listeners. And for a paltry sum."
OL,16,FVeteran campaigner, Eamon McCann, said
OL,17,Fhe believed the campaign could have a
OL,18,Fpositive outcome.
OL,3,CLocals voice opposition to BBC Radio
OL,4,CFoyle cuts at public meeting
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G4/6
